BEGIN_SOLUTION
The correct answer is ${BBOLD}A${EBOLD}.
Since \( V = \pi r^2 h \) and \( r \) is constant,
\( V \) and \( h \) are proportional to each other.  Thus,
\[
\frac{\Delta V}{\Delta h}
=
\frac{\pi r^2 \Delta h}{\Delta h}
=
\pi r^2
\]
is constant.
END_SOLUTION
